                    Will Irish eyes be smiling?
            </a>
        

    </div>

    
        <div class="entry-body">
            
                <a href="/nnbArticle/display/869" class="entry-body">
                    Buying an old brand whose proposition is no longer tied to consumer trends, and whose sales have been declining for 18 years, could be said to be dangerously optimistic. There are, after all, just two chances of the ailing Slim Fast brand being turned around &ndash; slim chance and no chance. But perhaps in acquiring SlimFast Glanbia has something else in mind? For the sake of its shareholders, let&rsquo;s hope so.
