            <a href="/nnbArticle/display/867" class="entry-title">
                    Reinventing breakfast
            </a>
        

    </div>

    
        <div class="entry-body">
            
                <a href="/nnbArticle/display/867" class="entry-body">
                    Faced with declining sales of traditional breakfast cereals, Quaker and Kellogg are trying something new and different, creating new brands instead of extending existing ones, offering artisanal brands that don&rsquo;t look anything like they&rsquo;ve come from a big company, and fielding more convenient product types and packages and new benefits.
                </a>
            
        </div>

        

